title: Trap Queen

description.plain:
“Trap Queen” is the gratifying tale of Fetty Wap and his girl teaming up in the drug game. (A “trap” is a place where drug deals happen.) A few months after releasing this song, the Paterson, New Jersey native signed to Lyor Cohen’s 300 Entertainment.

Nearly a year after it was released, the song became a crossover sensation, hitting the #2 spot on the Billboard Hot 100 chart.

Fetty spoke to Complex about his inspiration for the song:

I was just dealing with somebody at the time, and she was holding me down. We were building a lot, and I came up with the concept. She was my trap queen.

The term “trap queen” first appears in Gucci Mane’s 2006 song “Trap Gurl”.

Fetty told Maxim the “song doesn’t have anything to do with love, really…” It’s about a girl who “learned how to cook crack, and she kind of did it so good that she made enough for the both of us,” he says. “She knew how to stretch that shit.”

“It’s not like, ‘Oh, babe, I love you, let’s work for this,’… No, we’re about to go break the law, and we’re gonna have some fun.”
